<h1>Interest Calculation (s.69 County Courts Act 1984)</h1>

<p><strong>Principal claimed:</strong> {{currency total_principal}}</p>
<p><strong>Interest rate:</strong> {{interest_rate}}% per annum</p>
<p><strong>Interest start date:</strong> {{#if interest_start_date}}{{interest_start_date}}{{else}}Not specified{{/if}}</p>
<p><strong>Calculation date:</strong> {{generation_date}}</p>
<p><strong>Days of interest:</strong> {{#if interest_days}}{{interest_days}} days{{else}}Not calculated{{/if}}</p>
<p><strong>Daily rate:</strong> {{currency daily_interest}} ({{interest_rate}}% / 365)</p>
<p><strong>Accrued interest to date:</strong> {{currency interest_to_date}}</p>

<h2>Working</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Step 1 - Daily rate:</strong> ({{currency total_principal}} x {{interest_rate}}%) / 365 = {{currency daily_interest}} per day
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Step 2 - Interest accrued:</strong> {{currency daily_interest}} x {{#if interest_days}}{{interest_days}}{{else}}0{{/if}} days = {{currency interest_to_date}}
</p>

<h2>Interest continues</h2>
<p>
  Interest continues to accrue at {{currency daily_interest}} per day from {{generation_date}} until judgment or earlier payment.
</p>
<p>
  <em>Note: Update this calculation if you file after the above calculation date. You may claim interest up to and including the date of issue.</em>
</p>
